The man who allegedly attacked the world-renowned Ndebele artist, Esther Mahlangu has not been granted bail. Simon Skosana appeared at the Siyabuswa Magistrate Court in Mpumalanga on Wednesday. He allegedly broke into the 86-year-old’s home in March, tied her down and stole her possessions, including a firearm. She was also allegedly assaulted during the robbery. His case has been postponed to the 26th of April. Skosana is facing charges of robbery, assault, theft of a firearm and cash. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.